guidelines: You are more than the role you play; value your essence.
Remember: Discipline and depth open the doors to freedom.
Pace yourself, make time for relaxation, and stay healthy.
Find the courage to be as open and vulnerable as you can.
questions: When I feel limited or restricted, who can set me free?
Have I found a balance between dependence and independence?
What is my present level of discipline and focus?
Do I directly express what I really feel and need?
If these questions generate any insights, how might you put these insights into practice?

advice: A balanced, low-fat diet and regular exercise are both very important disciplines for 32/5s and 23/5s.
Their exercise regimen needs to include varied exercises that are fun and efficient. Cross training, moving to music, dancing, martial arts, and hiking are all excellent.
If they use drugs as a form of "adventure", they will eventually come, through hard experience, to learn that drugs can only enslave them.

opportunities: working with a variety of people

advice: Individuals do not necessarily find freedom in isolation.
Committed relationships provide the arena [for working through issues of cooperation with self and others].

Once they take responsibility for their own life and realize that they can become the writer and director in their own movie, they cease resenting others for 'stopping them' and find more freedom in cooperation than in reactive independence or isolation.
They need to find the courage to express what they feel.
They also need to acknowledge a desire for variety and adventure and find a way to fulfill this desire with their partner if they are in a committed relationship.
They often enjoy fantasies and playing different roles.
Their relationships and sexual play present an opportunity to experience new levels of liberation by breaking free of roles to find new levels of emotional authenticity and vulnerability.
negative: projecting their own lack of internal freedom onto their partner, companion, or children

seeing their relationship as a jail
positive: seeing their relationship as a doorway to deeper freedom and experience

advice: They appreciate a safe, secure home base (preferably with a fireplace), but when they come to their full confidence, 32/5s and 23/5s tend to trade security for adventure.
With the quick wit of 5s, they can usually find or create money when they need it and stay at least one step ahead of any creditors.
